# Gallery Project

A responsive image gallery built with **HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (MVC pattern)**.  
Displays images in a clean grid layout, allows adding favorites, viewing full-size images, and filtering by category.

## Features

- Responsive grid layout using **CSS Grid**
- Smooth hover effects (zoom and shadow)
- Lightbox-style image preview modal
- Add/Remove favorites with persistent storage
- Category filter to show specific image types
- Header navigation between **Home** and **Favorites**
- Organized using the **MVC (Model–View–Controller)** architecture

## File Structure

CodeAlpha_Gallery/  
├─ data/  
│   ├─ images/  
│   ├─ data.js  
│   ├─ generate_captions.py  
│   └─ images.json  
│  
├─ scripts/  
│   ├─ model.js  
│   ├─ view.js  
│   └─ controller.js  
│  
├─ styles/  
│   ├─ general.css  
│   ├─ header.css  
│   └─ home.css  
│  
├─ index.html  
├─ favorites.html  
└─ README.md  

## How to Use

1. Open `index.html` in your browser  
2. Browse images in the **Home** tab  
3. Click any image to open its full-size **preview modal**  
4. Use the **Add to Favorites** button to save images you like  
5. Go to the **Favorites** tab to view or remove saved images  
6. Use the **category selector** to filter images by type  

## Notes

- Image data (title, description, category) is stored in `data.js`  
- Favorites are saved using **localStorage**  
- Follows the **MVC architecture** for better organization and scalability  